content: Acknowledged. NCAT's Consumer and Commercial Division resolves a wide range of everyday disputes, including tenancy and other residential disputes, and consumer claims. The Consumer and Commercial Division deals with the following case types: housing and property, tenancy, social housing, boarding houses, residential communities, holiday parks, agricultural tenancy, strata schemes, community schemes, home building, retirement villages, dividing fences, consumers and businesses, consumer claims, motor vehicles, retail leases, agent commissions and fees, conveyancing costs, and pawnbrokers and second-hand dealers.
